This paper discusses the implementation of Mobile Ad-hoc Networks (MANET) using smartphones, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need for lightweight routing protocols, which involves the optimization of data transmission and storage, and can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the security concerns related to MANET, which can be categorized under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of routing protocols, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
